look at it and know exactly what to do.

09:23.250 --> 09:26.219
- Hello?
- Yes, I do, I just have to...

09:26.320 --> 09:29.908
- Was it something I said?
- No, I just have to make a phone call.

09:44.850 --> 09:46.838
What the fuck, Dude!

10:13.510 --> 10:14.810
What?

10:21.700 --> 10:25.753
-<i> You don't see anything unusual?</i>
- Where have you brought me?

10:26.020 --> 10:27.560
Look at the guy's sheet.

10:28.520 --> 10:31.520
- Why, why would I...
- Look, what do you notice?

10:35.280 --> 10:37.617
- He had a lotta priors.
- And?

10:37.667 --> 10:40.147
- "And", what "and"?
- All right, the girl's coming.

10:40.260 --> 10:43.120
Hi, I'll have a refill and...

10:44.850 --> 10:47.250
- Water.
- Okay.

10:48.380 --> 10:51.655
She never told me...
She had a pot in her hand...

10:51.705 --> 10:53.817
Okay, well, that's all right, she's probably...
where are you going?

10:53.920 --> 10:55.428
This place is freaking me out.

10:55.490 --> 10:58.149
Would you just hold on a second, please,
there... there... there's something to this...

10:58.199 --> 11:00.119
Could you just sit down...
humor me for a second.

11:00.220 --> 11:03.178
- Let's just talk about it tomorrow.
- Check out the guy's bail receipt.

11:08.020 --> 11:10.650
<i>Excuse me!</i>
'Scuse me!

11:16.160 --> 11:18.400
- Bro, this can't be right.
- It is.

11:19.030 --> 11:20.618
- How do you know?
- I checked.

11:20.668 --> 11:22.690
- Was it a bond?
- Cashier's check.

11:22.890 --> 11:25.062
- For $200,000?
- Yeah.

11:25.710 --> 11:28.380
- Who paid that?
- I don't know.

11:30.790 --> 11:32.360
What do you think?

11:33.170 --> 11:35.080
- What do I think?
-<i>Yes.</i>

11:36.050 --> 11:38.510
I think that guy has a
friend with deep pockets.

11:38.720 --> 11:41.819
That's deep, very deep.

11:43.310 --> 11:45.720
I think that guy's
getting a hand job.

11:46.100 --> 11:48.810
<i>He's still eating,
so it's hard to tell.</i>

11:49.310 --> 11:52.000
- Are you gonna have those, can I get one?
- What?

11:54.650 --> 11:57.290
<i>Who could get that much
cash together that quickly?</i>

11:57.340 --> 11:58.996
Wha... what's that for?

11:59.046 --> 12:00.989
- Have you ever tried it?
- I can't say that I have.

12:01.090 --> 12:02.820
All right, well, you take this one...

12:03.330 --> 12:04.409
and I'll take the other.

12:04.510 --> 12:07.128
What are we, in the sixth grade?
I'm not gonna eat this!

12:09.370 --> 12:15.319
He has cash in hand, I'm just sayin', if someone
risked a fortune to get this kid outta of jail,

12:15.420 --> 12:19.740
then, right now, you and I are the
only two people who even seem to notice.

12:20.510 --> 12:22.889
So, whaddya wanna do, ya want
me to rob a drug dealer for ya?

12:22.990 --> 12:25.510
Rob a drug dealer?

12:27.850 --> 12:31.125
Well, right now, I just wanna find
out where the cash is coming from.

12:32.310 --> 12:33.370
I don't think
it's a good idea.

12:33.490 --> 12:35.430
I'm not talking
about anything crazy.

12:35.650 --> 12:40.840
Look... look, this guy is a... well,
you read his sheet, he's a nobody.

12:42.160 --> 12:44.019
But he can't be a nobody,
who spends $200,000 on a nobody?

12:44.120 --> 12:46.481
If you want my opinion...

12:46.531 --> 12:50.067
Something like this it is worth doing
if you can keep it quiet and simple, okay?

12:50.117 --> 12:53.386
And what you're talking about here would be
neither of those things, I can promise you that.

12:53.436 --> 12:55.142
Wow, that sounded so cool.

12:55.770 --> 13:00.136
The way you just said that,
right now, that sounded cool.

13:04.920 --> 13:07.760
- What, it tastes good to you?
- Naw, it doesn't.

13:10.480 --> 13:13.801
Sometimes I think I
should really pull it together...

13:14.390 --> 13:16.044
a little bit.

13:16.770 --> 13:20.192
- I think they're checkin' us out.
- No, they're not.

13:20.242 --> 13:22.190
- I think they are.
- You're wrong.

13:23.850 --> 13:25.260
I just wanna put a tail on him.

13:25.351 --> 13:29.087
If it's a den then so be it, life
goes on, none the richer.

13:29.160 --> 13:31.785
I'll cover your time off.

13:35.850 --> 13:39.470
All right, I'll do it,
I'll find this guy.

13:39.760 --> 13:43.274
But only because when it come
to you and me, I truly, and...

13:43.350 --> 13:48.289
I mean this sincerely, I truly have
nothing better to do, and I despise my job.

13:48.390 --> 13:50.062
That's the spirit!

13:51.148 --> 13:53.855
You are a bad ass!

15:19.520 --> 15:21.136
What the fuck!

15:48.930 --> 15:50.380
What does he do in there?

15:50.481 --> 15:52.295
He works in the first floor restaurant.

15:52.350 --> 15:54.153
I know, but...what is it?

15:54.250 --> 15:59.080
You know, he gave us drinks, stocks the bar.
Could you stop that?

16:01.400 --> 16:03.280
Someone has him scared.

16:03.520 --> 16:06.021
- Whaddya mean?
- He shows up to work five nights a week...

16:06.120 --> 16:07.462
- Yeah.
- on time...

16:07.512 --> 16:09.074
- Yeah.
- to stock a bar?

16:09.124 --> 16:10.124
Uh-huh.

16:10.870 --> 16:12.650
He's a drug dealer, Dave.

16:20.000 --> 16:21.390
Jesus!

16:35.810 --> 16:40.680
<i>Jim! Jim! You can't just go
marching up to</i> this guy right now!

16:40.900 --> 16:42.690
- You're dressed like a cop.
- I am a cop.

16:42.790 --> 16:45.250
- You know what I mean!
- Look, you gotta give this another week at least.

16:45.374 --> 16:48.449
For what? The kid got rolled and now
his people have him cleaning dishes.

16:48.550 --> 16:50.122
Jesus! Will you stop looking around!

16:50.190 --> 16:52.476
- Are you sure you didn't miss something?
- Yes, I'm sure.

16:52.577 --> 16:55.350
Well, you're out there smoking
that refer, so you might not...

16:55.420 --> 16:58.119
I'm sorry? Am I on an official assignment here?

16:58.220 --> 17:00.989
Short of getting hired as bellhop,
there's nothing that more I can do.

17:01.040 --> 17:04.226
And I'm not wasting anymore
vacation days on this, either.

17:04.276 --> 17:07.228
Don't take this the wrong
way, because we're friends, and

17:07.278 --> 17:09.435
and you're also my boss...
fuck you, Jim!

17:09.486 --> 17:12.003
- This is some bullshit right here.
- David.

17:12.521 --> 17:15.913
David! Stay positive, Dude!

17:33.960 --> 17:37.852
I'm leavin' this with you guys,
Treasury'll be by to pick it up.

17:38.859 --> 17:40.227
It's all fake.

17:40.460 --> 17:42.018
- When are they coming?
- How should I know.

17:42.090 --> 17:46.690
- Come on, man, I got a lot of shit to do.
- Oh, God, sorry about that.

17:47.460 --> 17:49.450
Can't you just wait for 'em?

17:52.090 --> 17:54.100
I'll tell you what,
I'll flip you for it.

17:59.520 --> 18:01.026
What are you doing?

18:03.140 --> 18:05.172
Would you like to go first,
or should I?

18:05.230 --> 18:06.251
- You?
- Stop it.

18:06.301 --> 18:08.135
Okay, I'll go first.

18:10.290 --> 18:12.966
Jesus!Fuck!
What the...

18:13.400 --> 18:15.846
- That's a rush... your turn.
- No.

18:15.896 --> 18:17.567
- No?
- Oh fuck!

18:25.370 --> 18:26.594
-<i> Sergeant Waters.</i>

18:26.624 --> 18:30.810
What?
What's this about?

18:30.911 --> 18:34.389
<i>Lieutenant Stahl requested you for his desk
while he's away on a special assignment, Sir.</i>

18:35.050 --> 18:37.840
What are you talking about?
What special assignment?

21:52.290 --> 21:54.000
Jesus Christ!

21:55.580 --> 21:57.540
<i>Jimmy, it's your friend!</i>

21:58.880 --> 22:01.210
Where the hell are you
going at this hour?

22:01.470 --> 22:04.919
- Official Police business, Dad.
- Who's the cop?

22:05.590 --> 22:08.622
I am, Dad, we both are...
goodnight.

22:08.672 --> 22:11.669
- Good luck.
- Dad's unusually up-beat tonight.

22:11.720 --> 22:16.167
I know, yeah,
it's good to see, yeah, right?

22:23.740 --> 22:26.302
- What the fuck is this?
- It's my tips.

22:27.030 --> 22:29.870
Don't laugh,
it's more than we make.

22:36.630 --> 22:38.956
So, they're closed on Sunday.

22:40.670 --> 22:43.727
They do the drop-offs in the back,
but where does it go once it's inside?

22:43.777 --> 22:46.242
- Did you check it out?
- It's funny you should mention that.

22:46.280 --> 22:49.790
What, you didn't get hired
as a bag boy or something?

22:53.770 --> 22:56.565
- You take these?
-<i> There's one in there, that's...</i>

22:56.615 --> 22:58.724
Ah! Let's just see if you can spot it.

22:58.774 --> 23:00.802
- They're terrible.
- Yeah.

23:00.852 --> 23:02.589
It looks like a bum from
the street took these.

23:02.639 --> 23:05.607
Well, the Lord knows I wasn't
gonna go marching around back there.

23:06.030 --> 23:08.286
You made a homeless
person that these photos?

23:09.593 --> 23:11.270
Why... I paid them a little.

23:12.870 --> 23:14.660
- All right.
- Right.

23:15.270 --> 23:20.221
So, I think this is more than just a
money drop or however you call it.

23:20.370 --> 23:21.376
Why would you say that?

23:21.426 --> 23:24.059
Because whatever they're
bringing here, stays here.

23:24.550 --> 23:26.678
<i>Nothing goes out... ever.</i>

23:29.050 --> 23:31.330
- What is this?
- Huh?

23:33.520 --> 23:36.180
Look at the freezer, that lock.

23:38.060 --> 23:40.550
Makes you wonder, doesn't it?

23:41.520 --> 23:43.520
- Look at you.
- What?

23:43.730 --> 23:46.225
- And I'm skippin' right into your little...
- My what?

23:46.275 --> 23:47.966
What's the name of that
girl that solves the crimes.

23:48.070 --> 23:50.590
Nancy Drew...
this is some Nancy Drew shit.

23:51.680 --> 23:53.821
Did you see that one?

23:54.830 --> 23:56.320
Spotted it!

24:11.520 --> 24:13.180
It's that grocery store.

24:13.850 --> 24:16.260
I haven't heard anything from
your Department about this.

24:20.860 --> 24:22.639
- What kind of nonsense is this?
- No, no, I...

24:22.730 --> 24:24.410
- You just reached for my phone.
- Yes I did.

24:24.480 --> 24:26.190
- In a suspicious manner.
- No, I wasn't, I swear...

24:26.400 --> 24:28.869
I would suggest that you're here
under the auspice of illegal activity.

24:28.919 --> 24:31.411
- What crime is it anyway? You think...
- I'll call the Sheriff.

24:31.461 --> 24:33.490
- I'll give you $100.
- Okay.

24:36.200 --> 24:37.200
All right.

24:38.690 --> 24:43.830
Well, you are very lucky that this
investigation is so well funded, I'll tell you that.

24:50.450 --> 24:52.287
<i>Yeah, wipe it.</i>

24:52.430 --> 24:55.042
<i>- Wipe it.
- Delete, delete.</i>

24:55.600 --> 24:58.680
- Right there?
- Yeah, stop there, go a few frames back.

25:00.560 --> 25:03.140
<i>- Okay.
- Okay, stop, replay that.</i>

25:03.690 --> 25:06.381
<i>Okay, okay,</i> stop, can you
give me some other camera angles?

25:06.431 --> 25:07.791
Sure.

25:11.000 --> 25:12.000
<i>Now, pause it.</i>

25:13.940 --> 25:18.079
Isn't that that sandwich shop on Decatur,
the one that makes the cheese steaks?

25:18.180 --> 25:19.804
Oh, yeah, I've been
there, that place is legit.

25:19.900 --> 25:21.438
Man, that place is delicious.

25:21.940 --> 25:23.340
How ya doin', Bill?

25:26.250 --> 25:27.392
That's the way to go.

25:27.442 --> 25:28.811
<i>The way the cheese
spills over the bread.</i>

25:29.000 --> 25:31.202
- Hey, gotta get a cheeseburger.
- Jim!

25:31.252 --> 25:32.719
All right, give me a hard
copy of that, then wipe it,

25:32.820 --> 25:35.760
- and just keep goin' with the time codes there.
- You got it.

25:36.060 --> 25:38.160
- I looked at the store.
- Yeah?

25:38.770 --> 25:40.821
They recently installed
a new storage unit.

25:40.930 --> 25:43.662
<i>According to that work
order, that freezer has</i>

25:43.766 --> 25:47.540
<i>got 36 inches of steel
reinforced concrete protecting it.</i>

25:49.690 --> 25:52.098
<i>Now, it could be the world's
most secure meat locker,</i>

25:52.190 --> 25:53.575
<i>but when you consider
the drug dealers,</i>

25:53.650 --> 25:57.001
<i>the hotel front and phony laundry
service making one way trips to this place...</i>

25:57.070 --> 25:59.091
<i>And nothing ever goes out.</i>

26:00.120 --> 26:02.586
<i>I think you know exactly
what I'm getting at.</i>

26:03.180 --> 26:04.953
Holy shit!

26:08.560 --> 26:10.568
- Sir.
- Oh, thank you.

26:10.618 --> 26:12.442
- Wipe it?
- Wipe it.

26:18.100 --> 26:22.180
Have you ever broken
into a vault before?

26:23.350 --> 26:27.076
- No... are you serious right now?
- I don't know.

26:27.230 --> 26:28.730
- Have you?
- No.

26:28.860 --> 26:31.600
<i>- What about this one?</i>
- Yeah, go for it, Lewis.

26:32.610 --> 26:34.847
Ya know, here's a question:

26:34.940 --> 26:37.600
Somebody builds a safe in the
back of a grocery store, right?

26:37.724 --> 26:38.764
Yeah.

26:38.820 --> 26:40.933
- And we found it.
- Precisely.

26:40.980 --> 26:45.490
And we assume it's filled with money, or
drugs or whatever... it's filled with stuff?

26:45.750 --> 26:46.642
Yeah.

26:46.692 --> 26:51.668
Well... how do we...
ya know, get it... out?

27:21.740 --> 27:24.359
Hello, can I help you?

27:24.680 --> 27:26.607
Yes, hello.

27:26.710 --> 27:28.205
Just a moment.

27:28.854 --> 27:30.512
Just a moment.

27:33.804 --> 27:35.579
Yes, good.

27:36.010 --> 27:40.647
I need a drill.

27:42.100 --> 27:44.260
Wait... wait...

27:44.640 --> 27:47.518
How are you going to pay for it?

27:48.720 --> 27:52.250
Well, my people will contact you
and arrange it, ya, yes.

27:53.860 --> 27:56.707
The Yank's hiding something.

27:56.757 --> 27:58.825
He must be a bank
robber or something.

27:59.030 --> 28:01.333
Yeah, so cool.

28:11.420 --> 28:13.709
- I gotta go, you finish up.
-<i> But I'm not authorized.</i>

28:13.880 --> 28:15.750
Who gives a shit?

28:16.010 --> 28:19.690
<i>So this is the floor plan for the
apartment that's directly above the vault?</i>

28:19.995 --> 28:23.147
<i>- Yeah, taped it out this morning.
- You did a fine job.</i>

28:23.397 --> 28:24.383
<i>What's this?</i>

